3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-8-202 of Title 27A, unless
5 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. As used in this act:
7 1. "Eligible Landowners" means private, tribal, and public
8 landowners in Oklahoma counties within the Upper Red River Basin;
9 2. "Eradication" means the removal or substantial reduction of
10 salt cedar populations to a level where they no longer pose a
11 significant threat; and
12 3. "Salt Cedar" means all species within the genus Tamarix
13 identified as invasive or noxious in Oklahoma.
14 B. There is hereby created a program to control and eradicate
15 invasive salt cedar species in Oklahoma counties within the Upper
16 Red River Basin and is to be administered by the Oklahoma
17 Conservation Commission in collaboration with the Oklahoma
18 Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry and the Oklahoma Water
19 Resources Board. To accomplish the goals listed in this section,
20 the Commission is authorized to use the funds available in the Salt
21 Cedar Eradication Program Revolving Fund established in Section 3 of
22 this act. The purpose of the program is to manage and eradicate
23 invasive salt cedar species in Oklahoma counties within the Upper
24
