1 Red River Basin, to enhance water resources, restore native
2 ecosystems, and protect agricultural productivity.
3 C. The Oklahoma Conservation Commission, in collaboration with
4 the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry and the
5 Oklahoma Water Resources Board shall establish and oversee the Salt
6 Cedar Eradication Program which shall include:
7 1. Conducting surveys to identify and map salt cedar
8 infestations in Oklahoma counties within the Upper Red River Basin;
9 2. Developing and implementing science-based eradication
10 strategies, including mechanical removal, chemical treatments, and
11 biological controls;
12 3. Providing technical and financial assistance to eligible
13 landowners; and
14 4. Monitoring and evaluating the effectiveness of eradication
15 efforts.
16 D. The Oklahoma Conservation Commission shall establish
17 guidelines for participation, including cost-sharing arrangements
18 and reimbursement opportunities.
19 E. The Oklahoma Conservation Commission is authorized to
20 promulgate any rules and procedures to effectuate the provisions of
21 this act.
22 F. The Oklahoma Conservation Commission shall submit an annual
23 report to the Governor, Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
24 Representatives, the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State
