7 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
8 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-8-203 of Title 27A, unless
9 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
10 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
11 for the Oklahoma Conservation Commission to be designated the "Salt
12 Cedar Eradication Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a continuing
13 fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of
14 all monies received by the Oklahoma Conservation Commission from
15 appropriations, federal grants or funds, municipal contributions,
16 private contributions, and any other sources, including interest
17 earned from the income in the fund, that are designated for deposit
18 to such fund or designated for duties associated with removal and
19 eradication of salt cedars in Oklahoma counties within the Upper Red
20 River Basin. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are
21 hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
22 Conservation Commission to perform the duties imposed on the
23 Department by law. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon
24 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
